"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-life-style-paris-olympics-2024-closing-ceremony-details-b2593997.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  Tom Cruise gliding down the Stade de France, Billie Eilish and Snoop Dogg to take part in a 'science-fiction' and 'dystopia' themed event, and over a hundred performers, acrobats, dancers, and circus artists  Removed from bookmarks  I would like to be emailed about offers, events and updates from The Independent.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 530, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 216, \"end\": 226, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Cruise\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\"}, {\"begin\": 261, \"end\": 274, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billie_Eilish\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Billie Eilish\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billie_Eilish\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billie_Eilish\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice  After two weeks of intense, thrilling competition between the world's best athletes - not to mention a handful of controversies - theParisOlympicsare coming to an end.\", \"from\": 531, \"to\": 722, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Team GB secured over a dozen gold medalsfor performances in sports including swimming, mountain biking, shooting, rowing, and the men's triathlon, winning over 50 medals in total.\", \"from\": 724, \"to\": 903, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"USgymnast Simon Biles made a triumphant returnsecuring her seventh gold medal, while Swedish sports star Armand \\\"Mondo\\\" Duplantis won a gold medal for pole-vaulting, breaking the world record for the ninth time.\", \"from\": 905, \"to\": 1116, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Frenchswimmer L\\u00e9on Marchand won five medals - four of them gold - fulfilling comparisons toMichael Phelps, while Pakistan's Arshad Nadeem broke an Olympic record, and secured the first individual gold medal for the country.\", \"from\": 1118, \"to\": 1341, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1132, \"end\": 1145, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L\\u00e9on_Marchand\", \"score\": 0.9999997803538704, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"L\\u00e9on Marchand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L\\u00e9on_Marchand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L\\u00e9on_Marchand\"}, {\"begin\": 1217, \"end\": 1223, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\", \"score\": 0.9999999978826963, \"rank\": 2.1171997497272537e-09, \"text\": \"Phelps\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\"}, {\"begin\": 1231, \"end\": 1239, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\", \"score\": 0.9999985094375201, \"rank\": 1.2598901166928348e-06, \"text\": \"Pakistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, the games were not without controversy, asAlgeria's Imane Khelif battled a vicious gender rowafter she beat Italy's Angela Carini in 46 seconds.\", \"from\": 1343, \"to\": 1496, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1404, \"end\": 1416, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"score\": 0.9999996421621021, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Imane Khelif\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\"}, {\"begin\": 1460, \"end\": 1465, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"score\": 0.9962295972316421, \"rank\": 0.0037645834966661346, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\"}, {\"begin\": 1468, \"end\": 1481, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angela_Carini\", \"score\": 0.9999962103660394, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Angela Carini\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angela_Carini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angela_Carini\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After the opening ceremony was met withintense backlash for offending the Christian community, the secular state was forced to change the closing event for the \\\"umpteenth time\\\" in a bid to appease religious groups.\", \"from\": 1498, \"to\": 1712, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1572, \"end\": 1581, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christians\", \"score\": 0.7326857620469998, \"rank\": 0.21354967795497826, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The resulting celebration is said to be more considered so that \\\"we are not made to say what we do not want to say\\\", according to Thierry Reboul, executive director of both the opening and closing events.\", \"from\": 1713, \"to\": 1917, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1843, \"end\": 1850, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Augustin_Thierry\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.309971831756223e-22, \"text\": \"Thierry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Augustin_Thierry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Augustin_Thierry\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"TheRomanian prime minister has promised to boycottthe event after controversy surrounding a gymnastics ruling.\", \"from\": 1919, \"to\": 2029, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When is the 2024 Olympics closing ceremony?\", \"from\": 2031, \"to\": 2074, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The final game of the Olympics will be the women's basketball gold medal event which will take place at 2.30pm BST at the Bercy Arena in Paris.\", \"from\": 2076, \"to\": 2219, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2187, \"end\": 2190, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Summer_Time\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.744468814799214e-16, \"text\": \"BST\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Summer_Time\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Summer_Time\"}, {\"begin\": 2213, \"end\": 2218, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.257203707970544e-19, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The event will take place on Sunday 11 August and it is scheduled to begin at 8pm BST until 10.30pm BST.\", \"from\": 2221, \"to\": 2325, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2321, \"end\": 2324, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Summer_Time\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.744468814799214e-16, \"text\": \"BST\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Summer_Time\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Summer_Time\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It will take place in theStade de France, just north of Paris, with capacity for over 80,000 spectators, after the audacious opening ceremony took place at the Seine River.\", \"from\": 2326, \"to\": 2498, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2360, \"end\": 2366, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9893609584663022, \"rank\": 0.010737951145237231, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2382, \"end\": 2387, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.257203707970544e-19, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What will happen during the closing ceremony?\", \"from\": 2500, \"to\": 2545, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Traditional fixtures of the ceremony include the athletes' parade, handover of the Olympic flag to the organisers of the 2028 Los Angeles Olympics, and a final medal presentation ceremony (for the women's marathon from earlier in the day).\", \"from\": 2547, \"to\": 2786, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Organisers have promised \\\"over a hundred performers, acrobats, dancers and circus artists\\\".\", \"from\": 2788, \"to\": 2879, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And speculation has been rife as musical performances and \\\"the participation of world-renowned singers\\\" were confirmed to complete the picture.\", \"from\": 2880, \"to\": 3023, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Part of the show will take place in the air, while the giant sets, costumes, and spectacular lighting effects will take spectators on a journey through time, both past and future.\\\"\", \"from\": 3025, \"to\": 3206, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thomas Jolly, artistic director of both the opening and closing ceremonies added: \\\"It's a very visual, very choreographic, very acrobatic show with an operatic dimension to give a great visual fresco and say goodbye to athletes from all over the world.\\\"\", \"from\": 3208, \"to\": 3461, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3208, \"end\": 3214, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\", \"score\": 0.8724870500413456, \"rank\": 0.13045221038558388, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile organisers have promised a \\\"science-fiction\\\" and \\\"dystopia\\\" element to the show, which is named \\\"Records\\\".\", \"from\": 3463, \"to\": 3579, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Who will be performing?\", \"from\": 3581, \"to\": 3604, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The closing ceremony for the Paris Olympics will bring out several stars: Billie Eilish, Snoop Dogg.\", \"from\": 3606, \"to\": 3706, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3695, \"end\": 3705, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Snoop Dogg\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"H.E.R.\", \"from\": 3707, \"to\": 3713, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3707, \"end\": 3713, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/H.E.R.\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0002507278081352e-36, \"text\": \"H.E.R.\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/H.E.R.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/H.E.R.\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"and Red Hot Chili Peppers are scheduled to perform.\", \"from\": 3714, \"to\": 3765, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3718, \"end\": 3739, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Red_Hot_Chili_Peppers\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Red Hot Chili Peppers\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q215380\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Red_Hot_Chili_Peppers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Red_Hot_Chili_Peppers\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The all-star lineup will hit the stage as part of the handover to the 2028 Los Angeles Games.\", \"from\": 3767, \"to\": 3860, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"LA28 chairperson Casey Wasserman in a statement: \\\"This is the biggest moment in LA28 history to date, as the Olympic flag passes from Paris to LA.\", \"from\": 3862, \"to\": 4008, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3996, \"end\": 4001, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.257203707970544e-19, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We are thrilled to feature the very best of LA with local artists and are grateful to Billie, H.E.R., the Chili Peppers and Snoop for their collaboration on what will be an incredible show to a global audience that will give fans a taste of what's to come in 2028.\\\"\", \"from\": 4009, \"to\": 4274, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4103, \"end\": 4109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/H.E.R.\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0002507278081352e-36, \"text\": \"H.E.R.\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/H.E.R.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/H.E.R.\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Top GunstarTom Cruiseis said to be performing an \\\"epic stunt\\\" at the event.\", \"from\": 4276, \"to\": 4351, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"According to TMZ, theMission: Impossiblestar plans to rappel down from the top of Stade de France, land on the stadium field and carry the Olympic flag.\", \"from\": 4352, \"to\": 4504, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4434, \"end\": 4449, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stade de France\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While details of the closing ceremony are being kept top secret, it is known that LA Mayor Karen Bass will receive the Olympic flag from Paris Mayor Anne Hidalgo during the televised spectacle.\", \"from\": 4506, \"to\": 4699, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4597, \"end\": 4607, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Bass\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Karen Bass\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Bass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Bass\"}, {\"begin\": 4643, \"end\": 4654, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Mayor\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 4655, \"end\": 4667, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anne Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Expect a major Hollywood production,\\\"Deadlinereported, citing its own source.\", \"from\": 4701, \"to\": 4779, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4717, \"end\": 4726, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999999968168, \"rank\": 3.3083043379550233e-12, \"text\": \"Hollywood\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"How can I watch the closing ceremony?\", \"from\": 4781, \"to\": 4818, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For those in the UK, it will be live on BBC One, BBC iPlayer and the BBC Sport website and app.\", \"from\": 4820, \"to\": 4915, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4837, \"end\": 4839, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9959826861354368, \"rank\": 0.004033453930914222, \"text\": \"UK\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 4869, \"end\": 4872, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"score\": 0.9986424726826619, \"rank\": 0.0012954399202524942, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\"}, {\"begin\": 4873, \"end\": 4880, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_iPlayer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"iPlayer\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_iPlayer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_iPlayer\"}, {\"begin\": 4889, \"end\": 4898, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"score\": 0.9986085548202478, \"rank\": 0.001272617388644154, \"text\": \"BBC Sport\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Television coverage begins at 19:00 BST and there will be an accompanying live text.\", \"from\": 4916, \"to\": 5000, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4952, \"end\": 4955, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Summer_Time\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.744468814799214e-16, \"text\": \"BST\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Summer_Time\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Summer_Time\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Additional reporting by Agencies  Join thought-provoking conversations, follow other Independent readers and see their replies  Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 5002, \"to\": 5266, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5087, \"end\": 5098, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3547264488272287e-19, \"text\": \"Independent\", \"types\